I had been thinking about the possibility of a separate sub-command that opts you in / performs the decoration.  That seems the most transparent in terms of how it functions, but it has two distinct disadvantages: needs to be re-run if units are refreshed and if `deisctl` is used from multiple machines, probably only the one that the initial install was done from has units on disk that have the decoration.  Problems could occur if maintenance were performed later from a different machine.

I guess I like the first option better... just looking for feedback if you see any glaring issues with it.

