Just for the reference: v4 signatures are already supported. To make it work, you need to specify the region in your request. In your case:
```python
process.start({
    'input': 'upload',
    'file': open('music_test.mp3', 'rb'),
    "outputformat": "m4a",
    "output": {
        "s3": {
            "accesskeyid": "my-access-key",
            "secretaccesskey": "secret-key",
            "bucket": "bucket.name",
            "region": "us-east-2"
        }
    }
})
```

I went ahead and reverted linting these files. It's awkward because a `setup.py` file isn't actually an importable part of a module, it just defines the package. When you run mypy on these files, it errors because there are multiple `setup.py` files it has imported.

I have an unreverted version if we want it for some reason on the `leave-sys-out-of-this2` branch. Getting lint/mypy to work could be nice, but this PR as it is cleans things up a bit and I don't think blocking these small improvements on reworking some of our testing is necessary or a good use of our time right now. I'm happy to have an issue created for us to look into later though.

